    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The judge or other court officer (the Authority) informs the &lt;fen&gt;Accused&lt;/fen&gt; of the &lt;fen&gt;Charges&lt;/fen&gt; against him/her, i.e. the alleged actions and the relevant laws.
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Accused"&gt;The board&lt;/fex&gt; has been &lt;t&gt;accused&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Arraign_authority"&gt;by the federal court&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Charges"&gt;of making decisions based on narrow agendas and meddling where it shouldn't&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Arraign_authority"&gt;The police&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;charged&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Accused"&gt;a young nurse&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Charges"&gt;with four murders&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
Compare to: Citing.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
